description:
In the year 66 AD, a Jewish revolt against Roman rule escalated into a full-scale war that lasted four years. While most of Judea fell to the mighty Roman forces, one outpost stood defiant  the fortress of Masada, perched atop a barren plateau overlooking the Dead Sea.
This video explores the incredible tale of the Jewish Zealots who made their last stand against the Roman Empire at Masada. Built by Herod the Great as a refuge, this impregnable fortress was recognised for its natural defences and strategic advantages by figures like King David centuries earlier.
Witness the remarkable story of how a small group of Jewish rebels, driven by their unwavering spirit, defied the overwhelming power of Rome from their mountain stronghold. Discover the incredible engineering feat of Masada's construction and the determination of its defenders in the face of overwhelming odds.
Join us on this journey through history as we unravel the epic saga of Masada, a testament to the indomitable human spirit and the pursuit of freedom against all odds.
